Rating: 3
I've made these twice now, with great results both times. The first time, I followed the recipe except added tequila as I had no port on hand. The tacos were fabulous with a squirt of lime squeezed on at the table. I made them just last Saturday for a party. To spice the mix up, I added a 1/4 teaspoon of dried ground chipotle chile, substituted frozen sweet corn for hominy, added about a cup of leftover black bean/chicken enchilada filling and again substituted tequila for port. Served again with lime wedges on the side, a must I feel. Guests raved, husband raved, kid inhaled and ate the leftovers for lunch the next day with gusto. This will become a staple in my house.

Rating: 3
I made this for a dinner party and everyone loved it! I couldn't get hominy in time for the dinner so I just used frozen whole-kernel corn and that was great. I also added pineapple salsa to the mixture for some sweetness to balance the spice. Excellent.

