Rating: 4
These "tacos" were great! I didn't have port so I threw in some Marsala. For a delicious twist, stuff large spinach or sundried tomato tortillas with the filling, top with spinach queso (velveeta, rotel,& sauteed spinach) and serve with homemade guacamole salad!

Rating: 3
This is a very tasty dish. It's also low-fat and high-fiber, yet my husband (who normally only likes fat-filled concoctions) gives it three forks as well. And the coup de grace is it's easy to make. I've also used it for casual dinner parties, I just make rice and a salad and the guests assemble their own tacos, so the work on the hostess is minimal.

Rating: 2
I was all set to write a review claiming what a waste of good port, but I can't. This actually turned out to be quite tasty and a little sweet. Can't say I'll make it every week, but I'll make it again.

